results.title: Earth X: Appendix To Chapter One
Earth X Chapter Ten
results.description: Captain America and his army battle the Skull.   Black Bolt is revealed as the one who blinded the Watcher and prepares to attack the Celestials on his own.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Ten
results.description: Mr. Fantastic and the Watcher discuss Black Bolt's plans against the Celestials.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Eleven
results.description: Captain America kills the Skull.  Black Bolt dies fighting the Celestials, while Iron Man prepares to join the battle.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Eleven
results.description: Mr. Fantastic and the Watcher discuss Galactus' battle against the Celestials and Iron Man's impending death.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Twelve
results.description: Iron Man dies fighting the Celestials, in order to buy time for Galactus to arrive.  Loki attempts to convince the Asgardians that they are not Gods.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Two
results.description: Thing tells the Inhumans about the end of the Fantastic Four and Dr. Doom.  the Red Skull's army attacks Daredevil's circus.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Two
results.description: The Watcher and X-51 discuss the current state of the Fantastic Four and causes of the virus that has mutated the Earth.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Three
results.description: Namor battles the Skull's army while Mr. Fantastic learns about Vibranium from the Inhumans.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Three
results.description: X-51 and the Watcher discuss the Skull's army.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Four
results.description: The Skull's army chases off Captain America.  Mr. Fantastic and the Inhumans fail to get Vibranium from the Black Panther.  The Hulk meets with Clea.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Four
results.description: X-51 and the Watcher discuss the Celestials and the end of the human race.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Five
results.description: The Hulk dreams of Captain Marvel.  Loki sends Storm Giants to attack the Iron Avengers and Thor. Mr. Fantastic considers using Doom's time machine.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Five
results.description: X-51 and the Watcher discuss the fate of the Avengers, Norman Osborne's rise to power, and the lack of any psychics on Earth.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Six
results.description: Captain America sends a new generation of X-Men to Cyclops for training.  Mr. Fantastic finds Cerebro.  Hulk prepares to enter Death's realm in search of Captain Marvel.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Six
results.description: X-51 and the Watcher discuss the fates of various X-Men.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Seven
results.description: The Hulk enters the realm of the dead, and learns that Clea betrayed Dr. Strange to Loki.  The heroes gather in New York in preparation for the Skull's attack.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Seven
results.description: X-51 and the Watcher discuss the fates of the Hulk's friends and enemies, and learn that Nighthawk has seen the future of mankind.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Eight
results.description: The Skull attacks New York, destroying the Iron Avengers and Hydra.  Thor battles Clea and Loki.  Captain America works on building an international army.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Eight
results.description: X-51 discusses the Celestial's plans and the effects of the Terrigen Mists upon the Earth.

results.title: Earth X Chapter Nine
results.description: X-51 reveals the Celestials' plan to Mr. Fantastic.  Black Bolt is revealed to have been the one to mutate the Earth's populace.  The Skull kills President Osborne.

results.title: Appendix to Chapter Nine
results.description: X-51 reveals the secrets of the Celestials to Mr. Fantastic.

results.title: Earth X Chapter X
results.description: Franklin Richards becomes the new Galactus and drives off the Celestials.  Her becomes pregnant with the reincarnated Captain Marvel.  Mr. Fantastic finds a cure for the Terrigen Mists.
